<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Jim Power is Officially coming to NES.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12244&amp;p=139482#p139482"><![CDATA[
Actually, the second we announced the license with Jim Power I got an email from Huelsback people saying he owns the rights to the music. I asked them for proof, and they said &quot; oh well they were given to him in a phone call&quot;. The IP owner, which has been the original IP owner since Jim Power was born, said he had no recollection of that and if Huelsback wanted the music he could licensed it.<br /><br />By this time, they were pretty cool, even offered all the music in editable format for us to port to NES.<br /><br />Then, they went silent to this day. <br /><br />So all music is going to be kept original, but it is done from ground up on the NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6288">Piko</a> — Sat Jan 17, 2015 2:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
