<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-01-16T21:17:02-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-01-16T21:17:02-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12244&amp;p=139417#p139417</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12244&amp;p=139417#p139417"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Jim Power is Officially coming to NES.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12244&amp;p=139417#p139417"><![CDATA[
It's trying to make use of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulfrich_effect" class="postlink">Pulfrich effect</a>, an optical illusion in which darker images are processed later, causing circle strafing in the correct direction to be processed as depth. Wear a sunglass lens over one eye to see it. It was also used in a 1989 Diet Coke commercial and an episode of Doctor Who.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Jan 16, 2015 9:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
